==History== ===2012=== Radio Televisyen Brunei is one of the founder members in the ABU Radio Song Festivals, having participated in the very first [[ABU Radio Song Festival 2012]].<ref name="ABU Radio"/> Two songs were submitted for the first festival, with only one being selected to go through to the televised final. Maria Aires sang "Yang Terindah" and finished in third place, while Jazz Hayat failed to make it to the televised final.
===2014=== Brunei participated in the 2014 festival in [[Colombo]], [[Sri Lanka]], two songs were submitted by the Brunei broadcaster for the festival. On 19 March 2014 it was announced that Neff Aslee with the song "Juliet" had been put forward to participate,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=ABU Radio Song Festival 2014: More Songs Are Revealed|url=http://eurovoix.com/2014/03/19/abu-radio-song-festival-2014-more-songs-are-revealed/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=30 June 2015}}</ref> on 20 March 2014 Rapual Rezal was also announced as a potential participant.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Brunei: 2nd Song Entered Into ABU Radio Song Festival|url=http://eurovoix.com/2014/03/20/brunei-2nd-song-entered-into-abu-radio-song-festival/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=30 June 2015}}</ref> On 1 April 2014 it was confirmed that Neff Aslee had been selected to participate in the festival in Colombo.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=ABU Radio Song Festival: 12 Finalists Announced|url=http://eurovoix.com/2014/04/01/abu-radio-song-festival-12-finalists-announced/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=30 June 2015}}</ref>
===2015=== On 4 December 2014 Brunei confirmed that they would participate in the 3rd festival in [[Myanmar]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Brunei: ABU Radio Song Festival 2015 Participation Confirmed|url=http://eurovoix.com/2014/12/04/brunei-abu-radio-song-festival-2015-participation-confirmed/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=30 June 2015}}</ref> On 8 April 2015 it was announced that Nurul Huda Fadilah Hj Md Junaidi (Dila) would represent Brunei at the festival, she would sing “Aku Milik Orang”.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Brunei: ABU Radio Song Festival 2015 Entry Revealed|url=http://eurovoix.com/2015/04/08/brunei-abu-radio-song-festival-2015-entry-revealed/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=30 June 2015}}</ref>
