'''''Eugene Aram''''' is a [[melodrama|melodramatic]] novel by the British writer [[Edward Bulwer-Lytton]] first published in 1832. It depicts the events leading up to the execution of [[Eugene Aram]] in 1759 for murdering his business partner. 

==Adaptations==
{{Main|Eugene Aram (disambiguation)}}
The novel was adapted three times for silent films. 

