== 2014 == The following international trips were made by Prime Minister Matteo Renzi in 2014: {| class="wikitable" style="margin: 1em auto 1em auto" |- ! width=120|Country ! width=100|Areas visited ! width=90|Date(s) ! width=550|Notes |- |{{Flag icon|Tunisia}} [[Tunisia]] |[[Tunis]] |4 March |{{see also|Italy–Tunisia relations}} Prime Minister Renzi's [[state visit]] to [[Tunisia]] was his first trip outside Italy as head of the government. He chose Tunisia as the first foreign trip of his premiership in a demonstration of his new foreign policy towards [[Africa]]. Renzi met President [[Moncef Marzouki]] and Prime Minister [[Mehdi Jomaa]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=75014 Visita del Presidente del Consiglio in Tunisia]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|France}} [[France]] |[[Paris]] |15 March |{{see also|Italy–France relations}} Renzi's visit to [[France]] was his first trip in a country of the [[European Union]]. In [[Paris]], Prime Minister Renzi met French President [[François Hollande]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=75107 Visita del Presidente Renzi all'Eliseo]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Germany}} [[Germany]] |[[Berlin]] |17 March |{{see also|Italy–Germany relations}} Matteo Renzi went to [[Berlin]] where he met the German Chancellor [[Angela Merkel]], with whom discussed about the [[Crimean Crisis]] and the economic policies of the EU.<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=75122 Berlino: Renzi al vertice italo-tedesco]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|United Kingdom}} [[United Kingdom]] |[[London]] |1 April |{{see also|Italy–United Kingdom relations}} Renzi met in [[London]] the UK Prime Minister [[David Cameron]], the leader of the [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] [[Ed Miliband]] and the [[Mayor of London|Mayor]] of London [[Boris Johnson]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=75289 Visita del Presidente Renzi a Londra]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Belgium}} [[Belgium]] |[[Brussels]] |4–5 June |Prime Minister Renzi went in [[Brussels]] to participate to the [[40th G7 summit]]. The first one after the suspension of [[Russia]] from the [[G8]]. The main topics where the [[2014 pro-Russian unrest in Ukraine|Pro-Russian protests]] in [[Ukraine]] and the economic crisis.<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=75850 Renzi a Bruxelles per il G7 del 4-5 giugno]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Vietnam}} [[Vietnam]] |[[Hanoi]] |9–10 June |{{see also|Italy–Vietnam relations}} With his wife [[Agnese Landini]], Renzi started his official trip to [[Asia]], from Vietnam. He met [[President of Vietnam|President]] [[Trương Tấn Sang]] and [[Prime Minister of Vietnam|Prime Minister]] [[Nguyễn Tấn Dũng]], as well as [[Communist Party of Vietnam|Communist Party General Secretary]] [[Nguyễn Phú Trọng]]. In doing so, Renzi became the first Italian Prime Minister to officially visit Vietnam since 1973, when diplomacy first began between Italy and North Vietnam.<ref>[http://www.corriere.it/foto-gallery/politica/14_giugno_09/renzi-missione-asia-tappa-ad-hanoi-66179e40-efba-11e3-85b0-60cbb1cdb75e.shtml Renzi e la missione Asia, tappa ad Hanoi]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|China}} [[China]] |[[Beijing]] |10–12 June |{{see also|China–Italy relations}} In [[Beijing]] Renzi met [[President of the People's Republic of China|Chinese President]] [[Xi Jinping]] in [[Beijing]], who congratulated him for the "important reforms" being undertaken by his government. Xi also stated that China would continue cooperation with Italy ahead of [[Expo 2015]] in [[Milan]].<ref>[http://www.lastampa.it/2014/06/11/esteri/renzi-incassa-il-plauso-di-xi-jinping-congratulazioni-per-le-riforme-avviate-M7rKKrKy02gqhAJXqTzPfO/pagina.html Renzi in Cina: dobbiamo aprirci di più]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Kazakhstan}} [[Kazakhstan]] |[[Astana]] |12 June |Prime Minister Renzi met [[President of Kazakhstan|Kazakh President]] [[Nursultan Nazarbayev]] in [[Astana]], where they discussed withdrawal of [[Italian Army|Italian troops]] from [[Afghanistan]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=75925 Renzi in Vietnam, Cina e Kazakistan]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Belgium}} [[Belgium]] |[[Ypres]] |26 June |Matteo Renzi visited [[Ypres]] for the commemoration of the centenary from the [[First World War]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=76068 Renzi a Ypres per commemorazione Centenario Prima Guerra Mondiale]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Mozambique}} [[Mozambique]] |[[Maputo]] |19 July |Prime Minister Renzi's started a major trip to [[Africa]], meeting the [[President of Mozambique|Mozambique President]] [[Armando Guebuza]], with whom signed economic pacts to create investments by the Italian government-onwned oil company [[Eni]] in the African country for 50 billion dollars.<ref>[http://www.ilmessaggero.it/PRIMOPIANO/POLITICA/renzi_mozambico_eni_investimento_50_miliardi_descalzi_assicura_non_andremo_via_gela/notizie/806148.shtml#fg-slider-auto-74524 Renzi in Mozambico: «Da Eni un investimento da 50 miliardi». Descalzi assicura: «Non andremo via da Gela»]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Republic of Congo}} [[Republic of Congo]] |[[Brazaville]] |20 July |Matteo Renzi visited the [[Republic of Congo]] where he met President [[Denis Sassou Nguesso]], with whom he signed a cooperation for the extraction of [[oil]] in the country.<ref>[http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/topnews/2014/07/20/renzi-arrivato-in-congo-brazzaville_6f5254cc-dcaa-46bc-a0a0-ad2d6f969b96.html Renzi arrivato in Congo Brazaville]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Angola}} [[Angola]] |[[Luanda]] |20 July |Renzi met with [[President of Angola|Angolan President]] [[José Eduardo dos Santos]] in [[Luanda]]; it was the final stage of his trip to [[Africa]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=76285 Visita di Renzi in Mozambico, Congo-Brazaville e Angola]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Egypt}} [[Egypt]] |[[Cairo]] |2 August |{{see also|Egypt–Italy relations}} Matteo Renzi met [[President of Egypt|Egyptian President]] [[Abdel Fattah el-Sisi]] in [[Cairo]], holding talks about a variety of issues, including the [[2014 Israel–Gaza conflict|Israel-Gaza conflict]]. Renzi stated that Italy would support the Egyptian truce proposal, with the two leaders calling for an immediate cease-fire and the beginning of peace treaties.<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=76431 Renzi in Egitto per gli incontri istituzionali]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Iraq}} [[Iraq]] |[[Baghdad]] |20 August |{{see also|Iraq–Italy relations}} Renzi met the Head of State [[Fuad Masum]], Prime Minister [[Haider al-Abadi]] and his immediate predecessor [[Nouri al-Maliki]] to discussed about the [[Iraqi insurgency (2011-present)|insurgency]] of the [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|Islamic State]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=76536 Visita di Renzi in Iraq]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Iraqi Kurdistan}} [[Iraqi Kurdistan]] |[[Erbil]] |20 August |In [[Erbil]] Renzi met the President of [[Iraqi Kurdistan]] [[Mas'ud Barzani]] and Prime Minister [[Nechervan Barzani]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=76536 Visita di Renzi in Iraq]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|United Kingdom}} [[United Kingdom]] |[[Newport, Wales|Newport]] |4–5 September |{{see also|Italy–United Kingdom relations}} Prime Minister Renzi participated to the [[NATO]] Summit in Newport. |- |{{Flag icon|United States}} [[United States]] |[[New York City]] |21–26 September |{{see also|Italy–United States relations}} On 22 September, Renzi visited [[Silicon Valley]], [[California]], where he met young Italian emigrants who created [[Startup company|startup]]s in the USA.<ref>[http://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2014/09/22/news/i_cervelli_italiani_emigrati_nella_silicon_valley_spiegheremo_a_matteo_come_attirare_i_talenti-96368344/ cervelli italiani emigrati nella Silicon Valley: "Spiegheremo a Renzi come attirare i talenti]</ref> He also visited the headquarters of [[Twitter]], [[Google]] and [[Yahoo!]] to hold talks with chief executives. Renzi was accompanied by former [[Secretary of State|US Secretaries of State]], [[Condoleezza Rice]] and [[George Shultz]], and by the former American Ambassador to Italy, [[Ronald P. Spogli]].<ref>[http://www.lastampa.it/2014/09/22/italia/politica/cena-a-stanford-per-renzi-oggi-alla-silicon-valley-hCzgCJMfaHumDjWqFuPReO/pagina.html Cena a Stanford per Renzi, poi un tour digitale nelle sedi di Twitter, Yahoo e Google]</ref>
The following day, Renzi spoke at a [[United Nations]] summit in [[New York City]], focussing on the problem of [[climatic change]].<ref>[http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Renzi-al-summit-di-New-York-I-cambiamenti-climatici-sono-la-sfida-del-nostro-tempo-63e0de06-1c3a-4a1a-8c7c-feb2e360a58a.html Renzi al summit di New York: "I cambiamenti climatici sono la sfida del nostro tempo"]</ref> Following the summit, Renzi met former US President [[Bill Clinton]] and his wife, former Secretary of State [[Hillary Clinton]].<ref>[http://www.ilmessaggero.it/PRIMOPIANO/POLITICA/matteo_renzi_new_york_clinton_clima_america_usa/notizie/917888.shtml "Renzi a New York, incontro con i coniugi Clinton e l'assemblea dell'Onu"]</ref> At the end of his trip, Renzi participated in a reception offered by President [[Barack Obama]].<ref>[http://notizie.tiscali.it/feeds/14/09/23/t_121_20140923_POL_TN01_0106.html?ultimora "Renzi a New York: Via al vertice Onu su clima e incontro con Ban Ki-moon" ]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|United Kingdom}} [[United Kingdom]] |[[London]] |2 October |{{see also|Italy–United Kingdom relations}} Renzi met in [[London]] the Prime Minister of the United Kingdom [[David Cameron]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=76788 Renzi in visita a Londra]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Romania}} [[Romania]] |[[Bucarest]] |13 November |{{see also|Italy–Romania relations}} With his wife, [[Agnese Landini]], Renzi met in [[Bucarest]] the Prime Minister of the Romania [[Victor Ponta]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=77186 Renzi a Bucarest incontra il Primo Ministro della Repubblica di Romania]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Australia}} [[Australia]] |[[Brisbane]] |15–16 November |{{see also|Italy–Australia relations}} Matteo Renzi participated with his wife [[Agnese Landini]] at the [[2014 G20 Brisbane summit|G20 summit]] in [[Brisbane]]. Renzi had also a bilateral meeting with the Australian Prime Minister [[Tony Abbott]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=77181 Renzi al G20 a Brisbane]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Turkmenistan}} [[Turkmenistan]] |[[Ashgabat]] |18 November |In [[Ashgabat]], with Turkmen President [[Gurbanguly Berdimuhamedow]], Renzi signed a number of economic pacts securing increased gas supply.<ref>[http://www.agi.it/politica/notizie/turkmenistan_renzi_con_ashgabat_amicizia_anche_oltre_il_gas-201411180900-ipp-rt10030 Turkmenistan: Renzi, con Ashgabat "amicizia" anche oltre il gas] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402170009/http://www.agi.it/politica/notizie/turkmenistan_renzi_con_ashgabat_amicizia_anche_oltre_il_gas-201411180900-ipp-rt10030 |date=2 April 2015 }}</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Austria}} [[Austria]] |[[Vienna]] |24 November |{{see also|Italy–Austria relations}} Matteo Renzi met the Austrian Prime Minister [[Werner Faymann]] in [[Vienna]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=77291 Visita del Presidente del Consiglio a Vienna]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Algeria}} [[Algeria]] |[[Algiers]] |2 December |Renzi met in [[Algiers]] the Algerian President [[Abdelaziz Bouteflika]] and Prime Minister [[Abdelmalek Sellal]]. With the two leaders of the country, Renzi discussed the [[2014 Libyan crisis|Libyan crisis]], immigration from [[North Africa]], and also about gas imports from [[Algeria]] as an alternative to Russian imports, following the tensions between the European Union and Russia.<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=77350 Visita Renzi in Algeria]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Turkey}} [[Turkey]] |[[Istanbul]] |11 December |{{see also|Italy–Turkey relations}} On 11 December Renzi then travelled to [[Ankara]] for a second meeting with Erdoğan, during which Renzi expressed his support for [[Accession of Turkey to the European Union|Turkish accession]] to the [[European Union]]. On the same day he met [[Prime Minister of Turkey|Turkish Prime Minister]] [[Ahmet Davutoğlu]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=77401 Renzi in visita in Turchia]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Albania}} [[Albania]] |[[Tirana]] |30 December |Prime Minister Renzi met in [[Tirana]] the Albanian Prime Minister [[Edi Rama]] and the President [[Bujar Nishani]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=77552 Renzi in visita a Tirana]</ref> |}
== 2015 == The following international trips were made by Prime Minister Matteo Renzi in 2015: {| class="wikitable" style="margin: 1em auto 1em auto" |- ! width=120|Country ! width=100|Areas visited ! width=90|Date(s) ! width=550|Notes |- |{{Flag icon|UAE}} [[United Arab Emirates]] |[[Abu Dhabi]] |8 January |Renzi made his first official trip of the year when he met Crown Prince [[Mohammed Bin Zayed Al Nahyan]] in [[Abu Dhabi]] to address issues of foreign policy and economic issues such as [[Alitalia]]-[[Etihad Airways|Etihad]]. The two leaders discussed joint co-operation domains and enhancing trade exchange and cooperation in the energy and aerospace fields.<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=77645 Renzi in visita negli Emirati Arabi Uniti]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|France}} [[France]] |[[Paris]] |11 January |{{see also|Italy–France relations}} Matteo Renzi participated, with more than 40 world leaders and three million people, in the [[Republican marches|Republican March]] organised by President [[François Hollande]] after the [[Charlie Hebdo shooting]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=77658 Renzi a Parigi per la manifesta Je suis Charlie]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Switzerland}} [[Switzerland]] |[[Davos]] |21 January |{{see also|Italy–Switzerland relations}} Prime Minister Renzi participated to the [[World Economic Forum]] in [[Davos]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=77709 Renzi al World Economic Forum]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|France}} [[France]] |[[Paris]] |24 February |{{see also|Italy–France relations}} Prime Minister Renzi participated to a bilateral meeting in [[Paris]] with the French President [[François Hollande]]<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=77952 Renzi a Parigi per il vertice italo-francese]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Ukraine}} [[Ukraine]] |[[Kyev]] |4 March |{{see also|Italy–Ukraine relations}} Renzi met in [[Kyev]] the President of [[Ukraine]], [[Petro Poroshenko]]; the meeting was focused on the [[War in Donbass]]. During the press conference, Renzi stated that: "Italy and the EU will continue to work together to implement the [[Minsk II|Minsk accord]] and doing all we can to return to peace with the respect of the integrity and sovereignty of Ukraine."<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=77999 Renzi a Kiev incontra Poroshenko]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Russia}} [[Russia]] |[[Moscow]] |5 March |{{see also|Italy–Russia relations}} Matteo Renzi met Russian President [[Vladimir Putin]] and Prime Minister [[Dmitry Medvedev]] in [[Moscow]]. The talks between the leaders was focused on international issues, such as settlement of the crisis in Ukraine, the situations in the [[Middle East]] and in [[Libya]], as well as fighting terrorism. Putin guaranteed Russian support in case of a [[United Nations|UN]] intervention in Libya against the [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|Islamic State]]<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=78013 Renzi a Mosca, incontri con Medvedev e Putin]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Egypt}} [[Egypt]] |[[Sharm el-Sheik]] |13 March |{{see also|Egypt–Italy relations}} Renzi participated to the Egypt Economic Development Conference with the President [[Abdel Fattah el-Sisi]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=78054 Renzi in Egitto]</ref> |- |{{flagicon|Tunisia}} [[Tunisia]] |[[Tunis]] |29 March |{{see also|Italy–Tunisia relations}} Renzi participated in a march organised by the Tunisian government after the [[Bardo National Museum attack]].<ref>[http://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2015/03/29/news/tunisia_marcia_renzi-110743644/ A migliaia a Tunisi contro terrorismo: "Le monde est Bardo". Ucciso leader jihadista]</ref> |- |{{flagicon|Malta}} [[Malta]] |[[Valletta]] |8 April |{{see also|Italy–Malta relations}} Matteo Renzi visited [[Malta]], where he met the Prime Minister [[Joseph Muscat]], discussing about the illegal immigration in the [[Mediterranean Sea]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=78266 Renzi in visita nella Repubblica di Malta]</ref> |- |{{flagicon|United States}} [[United States]] | [[Washington D.C.]] |16–17 April |{{see also|Italy–United States relations}} At the [[White House]] Renzi discussed, with President Obama, about many issues, including [[War in Donbass|Ukraine]], [[Libyan Civil War (2014–present)|Libya]] and [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|Islamic State]]. They also talked about Europe's economy, a pending trade pact between the U.S. and Europe, climate change and energy security.<ref>[https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2015/04/17/obama-italian-prime-minister-renzi-to-meet-at-white-house Obama, Renzi meet at White House]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Germany}} [[Germany]] |[[Schloss Elmau]] |7–8 June |{{see also|Italy–Germany relations}} Prime Minister Renzi went in [[Schloss Elmau]] to participate to the [[41st G7 summit]]. The leaders reached amo agreement on [[CO2 emission]] and [[global warming]].<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.it/2015/06/08/g7-schloss-elmau-clima_n_7534306.html G7 Schloss Elmau, accordo sul clima: tetto di 2 gradi all'aumento delle temperature. Renzi: "Al tavolo da protagonisti"]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Germany}} [[Germany]] |[[Berlin]] |1 July |{{see also|Italy–Germany relations}} Matteo Renzi met in Berlin Chancellor [[Angela Merkel]]. They discussed about the [[Greek debt crisis]] and the [[Greek bailout referendum, 2015|bailout referendum]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=78873 Renzi a Berlino il 1 luglio]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Ethiopia}} [[Ethiopia]] |[[Addis Ababa]] |14 July |{{see also|Ethiopia–Italy relations}} Renzi visited Addis Ababa where he met the President [[Mulatu Teshome]] and Prime Minister [[Hailemariam Desalegn]].<ref>[http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2015/07/14/renzi-arrivato-in-etiopia_7150ec97-af62-4265-b746-74e60bf72033.html Renzi in Etiopia]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Kenya}} [[Kenya]] |[[Nairobi]] |15 July |{{see also|Italy–Kenya relations}} Matteo Renzi met the Keyan President [[Uhuru Kenyatta]] and spoke at the [[University of Nairobi]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=78970 Renzi in Etiopia e Kenya]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Israel}} [[Israel]] |[[Tel Aviv]], [[Jerusalem]] |21–22 July |{{see also|Israel–Italy relations}} Prime Minister Renzi had a bilateral meeting with Prime Minister [[Benjamin Netanyahu]] and spoke to the [[Knesset]], on the following day.<ref>[http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/topnews/2015/07/21/renzi-arrivato-in-israele_5b6647a6-a8e3-4217-a687-adc3f08966f2.html Renzi arrivato in Israele]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Palestine}} [[State of Palestine|Palestine]] |[[Ramallah]] |22 July |{{see also|Israel–Palestine relations}} Matteo Renzi met the President of the Palestinian National Authority [[Mahmoud Abbas]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=79019 Renzi in visita in Israele e Palestina]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Japan}} [[Japan]] |[[Tokyo]], [[Kyoto]] |2–4 August |{{see also|Italy–Japan relations}} Renzi had a bilateral meeting in Tokyo with Prime Minister [[Shinzō Abe]] and was received at the [[Japanese Imperial Palace]] by the Emperor [[Akihito]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=79082 Renzi in Giappone dal 2 al 4 agosto]</ref> |- |{{flagicon|United States}} [[United States]] | [[New York City]] |26–29 September |{{see also|Italy–United States relations}} Prime Minister Renzi travelled to New York City to attend the seventieth session of the [[United Nations General Assembly]]. In his address, Renzi expressed Italy's support to "politically solve" the [[Syrian Civil War]], as well as to alleviate climate change.<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=79381 Renzi a New York per l'Assemblea Generale delle Nazioni Unite]</ref> |- |{{flagicon|Chile}} [[Chile]] | [[Santiago]] |23–24 October |{{see also|Chile–Italy relations}} Matteo Renzi met the Chilean President [[Michelle Bachelet]] at the presidential palace [[La Moneda]], inaugurating several renewable energy projects promoted by [[Enel]]. The Prime Minister spoke also at the [[University of Chile]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/Notizie/Palazzo%20Chigi/dettaglio.asp?d=79522 Visita del Presidente del Consiglio Renzi in Cile]</ref> |- |{{flagicon|Peru}} [[Peru]] | [[Lima]],<br>[[Machu Picchu]] |25–26 October |{{see also|Italy–Peru relations}} Renzi visited the sanctuary of [[Machu Picchu]] with the Prime Minister [[Pedro Cateriano]]. On the following day he went to Lima, where he met the Peruvian President [[Ollanta Humala]].<ref>[https://it.notizie.yahoo.com/foto/perù-il-presidente-humala-accoglie-slideshow-173324818/ Perù, il presidente Humala accoglie il premier Matteo Renzi]</ref> |- |{{flagicon|Colombia}} [[Colombia]] | [[Bogotà]] |27 October |{{see also|Colombia–Italy relations}} Prime Minister Renzi met the President [[Juan Manuel Santos]], promoting new energetic treaties.<ref>[http://www.ilpost.it/2015/10/28/matteo-renzi-colombia/ L’entusiasmo di Renzi per la Colombia]</ref> |- |{{flagicon|Cuba}} [[Cuba]] | [[Havana]] |28 October | Matteo Renzi became the first Italian Prime Minister to visit Cuba. In Havana he met President [[Raúl Castro]]; he was the first [[G7]] leader to visit Cuba after the normalization of relations between Cuba and the [[United States]].<ref>[http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2015/10/26/renzi-in-peru-le-cose-si-possono-cambiare-litalia-e-tornata_bfb02025-b215-4c58-b6e9-7760a1f41bc3.html Renzi a Cuba incontra Raul Castro e cena all'Avana. Rientro in Italia nel pomeriggio]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Saudi Arabia}} [[Saudi Arabia]] |[[Riyahd]] |8–9 November | Prime Minister Renzi met the King of Saudi Arabia [[King Salman]], with whom signed lot of economic cooperation pacts between the two countries.<ref>[http://www.polisblog.it/post/362254/matteo-renzi-visita-arabia-saudita-ultime-notizie Matteo Renzi in visita in Arabia Saudita: oggi l'incontro con Re Salman]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Turkey}} [[Turkey]] |[[Antalya]] |15–16 November |{{see also|Italy–Turkey relations}} Matteo Renzi participated at the [[2015 G-20 Antalya summit|G20 summit]] in [[Antalya]], hosted by President [[Recep Tayyip Erdoğan]]; the summit was focused on the fight to the [[Islamic State of Iraq and Levant]].<ref>[http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/G20-sul-tavolo-del-summit-irrompe-il-terrorismo-Bilaterale-tra-Renzi-e-Putin-e1d00758-25c6-465e-8c71-1869de0a1902.html G20, sul tavolo del summit irrompe il terrorismo, bilaterale tra Renzi e Putin]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|France}} [[France]] |[[Paris]] |25 November |{{see also|Italy–France relations}} Prime Minister Renzi participated to a bilateral meeting in [[Paris]] with the French President [[François Hollande]], focused on the fight to ISIL. It was the first meeting with Hollande, after the [[November 2015 Paris attacks|November Paris Attack]]. Renzi had also a ''lectio magistralis'' to [[Sorbonne University]].<ref>[http://governo.it/agenda/2015-11-26t000000/parigi-incontro-bilaterale-renzi-hollande-e-lectio-magistralis/3260 Parigi, incontro bilaterale Renzi-Hollande e Lectio Magistralis]</ref> |- |{{Flag icon|Lebanon}} [[Lebanon]] |Shama |22 December |{{see also|Italy–Lebanon relations}} Renzi visited the Italian troops in [[Lebanon]], who took part to the [[United Nations]] peacekeeping mission [[UNIFIL]].<ref>[http://www.ilpost.it/2015/12/22/matteo-renzi-libano/ Le foto di Matteo Renzi in Libano]</ref> |}
