{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}} {{Use Australian English|date=August 2015}} {{Infobox music festival | name = Summadayze | image = File:Seth Troxler.jpg | caption = [[Seth Troxler]] at SummaDayze 2012 in Melbourne | location = Australia, New Zealand | years_active = 1998-2013 | founders = [[Future Entertainment]] | dates = | genre = [[Electronic music]], | attendance = | capacity = | website =[http://www.futureentertainment.com.au/summadayze/ Summadayze] }} '''Summadayze''' was an annual Australian music festival held in the month of January. The first event occurred on 1 January 1998 at the [[Sidney Myer Music Bowl]] in [[Melbourne]]. It subsequently expanded into a four city festival including one in New Zealand. Summadayze was organised by [[Future Entertainment]] before it was liquidated in 2013.<ref name="liq">{{Cite news |url=https://tonedeaf.com.au/future-entertainment-liquidation-begins-as-summadayze-cancelled/ |title=Future Entertainment Liquidation Begins, As Summadayze Cancelled |author=Al Newstead |accessdate=4 June 2018 |date=9 September 2013 |website=Tonedeaf.com.au |publisher= Seventh Street Media}}</ref>
Summadayze was held at Doug Jennings Park on the [[Gold Coast, Queensland|Gold Coast]] in 2003. In 2004, the Summadayze festival was held in Melbourne, Gold Coast, [[Auckland]] and [[Perth]]. The 2006 event in Melbourne saw 23,000 tickets sellout for a 15-hour event.<ref name="hdw">{{Cite news |url=http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2006/01/01/1136050346195.html |title=Happy dayze with a bubble feature at the bowl |author=Carolyn Webb |accessdate=16 September 2013 |date=3 January 2006 |newspaper=The Age |publisher=Fairfax Media }}</ref> 35 drug-related arrests were made.<ref name="pdu">{{Cite news |url=http://www.theage.com.au/news/national/police-dog-units-to-target-rave-parties/2006/01/02/1136050393318.html |title=Police dog units to target rave parties |author=Jesse Hogan |accessdate=16 September 2013 |date=3 January 2006 |newspaper=The Age |publisher=Fairfax Media}}</ref> In 2011, events were again held in Melbourne, Adelaide, Gold Coast and Perth.<ref name="slu">{{Cite news |url=http://www.abc.net.au/triplej/musicnews/s2980755.htm |title=Summadayze line-ups for Melbourne, Adelaide, Gold Coast and Perth |accessdate=16 September 2013 |date=12 August 2010 |work=Triple J |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation }}</ref> The Melbourne event saw 59 people arrested on drugs charges.<ref name="saa">{{Cite news |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2011-01-02/scores-arrested-at-melbourne-music-festival/1891590 |title=Scores arrested at Melbourne music festival |author=Jack Kerr |accessdate=16 September 2013 |date=2 January 2011 |work=ABC News |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation }}</ref>
